                <h1>Jesse Owens: Journey Through Education and Athletics</h1>
                <p>Jesse Owens attended Fairmont Junior High School and later transferred to East Technical High School in Cleveland, where he excelled in track and field. His remarkable athletic talent emerged during his college years at Ohio State University, where he broke several world records and won four gold medals at the 1936 Berlin Olympics.</p>
